<H3> <TI>   Minister Gives Statistics on AIDS in Kerala </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WE0192A New Delhi PATRIOT in English 25 Jan 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> 94WE0192A </F>
<F P=104>  New Delhi PATRIOT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Thiruvananthapuram -- Eleven people have died of 
AIDS in Kerala so far, Health Minister R. Ramachandran Nair told 
the State Assembly today. 
  In written replies to questions by Mr. M.M. Hassan 
(Congress) 
and others, he said there were 56 AIDS patients in the State now. 
  He said 302 people in the State were infected with HIV. 

</TEXT>

