<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Missiles No Longer Targeted on U.S., Britain </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203155294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1456 GMT 12 Mar 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1203155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Boris Yeltsin signed a decree charging the 
Defense Ministry with outlining and carrying out by May 30 a 
package of measures to organize the daily activities of 
strategic nuclear forces equipped with non-targeted missiles. 
  As INTERFAX learned at the presidential press service, the 
decree is aimed at implementing the Moscow Declaration signed by 
the Russian and U.S. presidents on January 14 and the joint 
statement by the Russian president and the British premier of 
February 15. 
  These documents said that Russian nuclear missiles will no 
longer be targeted against the USA and Great Britain. 
  By another decree Boris Yeltsin set up a commission on 
supreme military ranks and high military and specialized schools 
of the Presidential Council for Personnel Policy. The Russian 
presidential aide for national security Yury Baturin was 
appointed as the chairman of the commission, the presidential 
press service reported. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

