<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Swiss Chemical Company To Expand Chinese Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0902101594 Bern ATSA/SDAA in French 1741 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BR0902101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern ATSA/SDAA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed DC/AL: "Ciba Expands Its Activities in </F>
China"; as released by Bern ATSA/SDAA database] 
  [Text] Basel, 7 Feb (ATS) -- The Basel-based chemicals and 
pharmaceuticals group Ciba is extending its plant protection and 
pigment activities to China. According to a statement released 
Monday evening, a contract was signed Monday for the creation of 
the first Chinese subsidiary of Ciba's plant protection 
division. In addition, Ciba's pigments division has concluded a 
joint venture with a Chinese company. Ciba is one of the most 
active foreign investors in China. 
  With a capital base of 18 million francs, the new plant 
protection company, Ciba Agro Ltd., has been established in 
Kunshan [name as received] (province of Kiangsu). It will 
employ some 240 people once its activities, which are planned 
for 1996, begin. Ciba holds 95 percent of the capital of Ciba 
Agro (Kiangsu) Ltd., according to the statement. 
  Ciba's pigments division concluded an agreement on the 
production of organic pigments as part of a joint venture with 
the Chinese company Qingdao Dyestuffs Factory. The plant should 
be commissioned in Qingdao [name as received] (province of 
Shantung) in late 1996. Qingdao Dyestuffs Factory is one of 
China's leading producers of dyes, while Ciba's pigments 
division is the world's largest producer of pigments. 

</TEXT>

