<H3> <TI>   Expert Terms Official Data on Toxins `Very Conservative' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003230094 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1003230094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Official data on chemical weapons in Russia is very 
conservative, thinks Aleksey Yablokov, chairman of the Russian 
Security Council's Interdepartental Commission for Ecological 
Safety. According to Interfax, he declared this at a news 
conference today. He said that in Russia there are not 40,000 
tonnes of toxic substances, as officially stated, but possibly a 
whole order of magnitude more. 
  Apart from Aleksey Yablokov, the news conference was also 
attended by Lev Fedorov, a doctor of chemical sciences and 
co-author of the scientist Vil Mirzoyanov, who published the 
well-known article Poisoned Politics [Otravlennaya politika]. 

</TEXT>

