<F P=100> AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> SOMALIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Italian Aid Workers Kidnapped for Ransom </TI></H3>
<H4>   Ransom Demand for Kidnapped Italians </H4>
<F P=102> LD1302181194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1750 GMT 
13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1302181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The bandits who kidnapped the two Italian aid 
workers have made a ransom demand. The terms of the demand have 
not yet been released. 
  The news was communicated by Marco Benassi, director of the 
European Agricultural Training Consortium [CEFA], who received 
the news in a telex sent from CEFA's office in Mogadishu. 
  Benassi said that the kidnapping of Gianfranco Stefani and 
Sergio Passadore was "a new way of extorting money." 

</TEXT>

